void print(double x)
{
    std::cout << "double " << x << '\n';
}

int main()
{
    short s { 5 };
    print(s);

    return 0;
}Show SolutionThe output isint 5. Converting ashortto anintis a numeric promotion, whereas converting ashortto adoubleis a numeric conversion. The compiler will favor the option that is a numeric promotion over the option that is a numeric conversion.1b) Why won’t the following compile?#include <iostream>

